==English==
===Etymology===
{{L.}} '''[[incubare]]''' (to lie in or on), from '''in-''' (in, on) + '''[[cubare]]''' (to lie); cf. [[succubus]]. Probably akin to Korean '''[[굽다]]''' (''gubda'': to lie on, etc.) cf. '''[[눕다]]''' (''nubda'': to lie on one's back cf. [[nubile]]). [You may observe the different bodily poses from those initials, ㄱ and ㄴ, of both Korean words.]

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''incubus''' (plural: [[incubi]])
# an [[evil]] [[spirit]] supposed to have [[sex]] with [[women]] as they [[sleep]]
# a [[nightmare]]
